15:32.348 --> 15:33.895
So, Tucker,

15:33.896 --> 15:35.256
we can do this, right?

15:35.257 --> 15:37.281
Be mature co-godfathers together?

15:38.165 --> 15:39.424
Just remember one thing:

15:40.777 --> 15:41.940
I'm in charge.

15:45.742 --> 15:49.031
Hey, man, this is a brand-new suit.

15:51.487 --> 15:53.556
Well, let me wash it for you.

15:53.557 --> 15:55.423
No, you did not just flick at me again.

15:55.906 --> 15:57.313
Hey hey hey.

15:57.314 --> 15:59.578
This place is sacred.
What the hell are you two doing?

15:59.579 --> 16:02.243
Damn! I just said "hell."
Crap! I just said "damn."

16:03.319 --> 16:04.165
Never mind.

16:04.166 --> 16:05.290
You two, stop fighting.

16:05.870 --> 16:07.665
Hi, aunt Betty, right?

16:08.172 --> 16:09.572
Who are you, dear?

16:09.573 --> 16:11.054
Well, you probably don't remember me,

16:11.055 --> 16:13.083
but I actually met you
when I was a little girl.

16:13.084 --> 16:14.356
Oh yes, of course.

16:14.672 --> 16:16.316
You're the chubby
little know-it-all

16:16.317 --> 16:17.703
who lived across the street.

16:19.039 --> 16:20.513
I'm the godmother you know.

16:22.041 --> 16:23.777
Okay, so I think we're all good.

16:23.778 --> 16:25.082
Priest, baby,

16:25.083 --> 16:26.518
<i>godfathers, godmother,</i>

16:26.922 --> 16:29.129
one more-or-less
happy couple,

16:30.215 --> 16:32.402
and one big-hearted,
generous great-aunt.

16:33.170 --> 16:34.854
Let's make some memories, people.

16:37.778 --> 16:39.376
Here, I wrote your vows.

16:39.750 --> 16:42.285
Oh, okay.

16:42.624 --> 16:44.911
"My dearest darling Bonnie,

16:45.221 --> 16:47.126
you are more beautiful today

16:47.127 --> 16:48.599
than the day I met you."

16:52.617 --> 16:54.388
Uh, "please forgive me

16:54.389 --> 16:55.897
for all of the many

16:55.898 --> 16:58.466
many mistakes I've made.

16:59.013 --> 17:01.812
I am the luckiest man in the world."

17:02.607 --> 17:03.859
Okay, what does yours say?

17:04.318 --> 17:06.118
"We both know I could do better."

17:06.119 --> 17:07.598
All right, people, let's do this.

17:09.060 --> 17:11.403
Dearly beloved, we are
gathered here today...

17:11.404 --> 17:12.665
What is going on?

17:13.609 --> 17:15.078
- Steve?
- Steve?!

17:15.079 --> 17:16.294
Hey, Steve.

17:17.258 --> 17:18.246
What are you doing here?

17:18.569 --> 17:20.644
Oh, my bad. I invited him.

17:21.497 --> 17:24.147
Yeah yeah. To a christening, not a wedding.

17:24.148 --> 17:26.079
Well, I didn't know about the wedding.

17:26.080 --> 17:28.715
And I thought the christening
might bring you two back together.

17:28.716 --> 17:30.405
Bring who back together?

17:30.963 --> 17:32.399
Me and Riley.

17:32.400 --> 17:33.974
She keeps throwing herself at me

17:33.975 --> 17:36.444
and trying to replace my
late wife, but no one can.

17:37.238 --> 17:38.458
And believe me,

17:38.459 --> 17:41.853
he has tried many times
to replace his late wife.

17:43.241 --> 17:45.083
Again, this is not a good time.

17:45.084 --> 17:46.517
I can't believe you won't marry me,

17:46.518 --> 17:48.804
but you'll marry that woman twice.

17:48.805 --> 17:50.391
Great dress by the way.

17:50.392 --> 17:51.435
Thank you.

17:52.185 --> 17:53.711
Can we just talk about this later?

17:53.712 --> 17:55.459
Which would be great
because I actually have

17:55.460 --> 17:56.984
a funeral in about half an hour.

17:57.908 --> 17:59.717
There's nothing to talk about, Ray.

18:00.249 --> 18:02.256
- We're done.
- Would somebody please

18:02.257 --> 18:04.161
explain to me what's going on here?

18:05.102 --> 18:07.011
Oh, now you want the
know-it-all's help.

18:08.148 --> 18:09.462
Okay, everybody, wait.

18:09.821 --> 18:12.056
This is not the example we
should be setting for Emma.

18:12.669 --> 18:14.801
We're supposed to be her
guides and a moral compass

18:14.802 --> 18:16.221
and all we're doing is lying.

18:17.429 --> 18:18.393
Aunt Betty,

18:18.748 --> 18:20.214
Emma's mom isn't dead.

18:20.627 --> 18:23.352
She left her on my doormat
after a one-night stand.

18:23.848 --> 18:26.566
And mom and dad got divorced two years ago.

18:26.946 --> 18:28.727
And dad's gay now

18:28.728 --> 18:30.467
and this is his boyfriend Steve.

18:33.034 --> 18:35.997
And you should make a commitment already.
He seems perfect for you.

18:35.998 --> 18:37.877
See? Told you.

18:42.407 --> 18:43.917
Look, aunt Betty,

18:44.699 --> 18:46.618
I really don't care what you think of us

18:47.581 --> 18:50.130
'cause I think we're pretty
darn perfect the way we are.

18:51.287 --> 18:52.283
And...

18:52.284 --> 18:54.321
And you did all of this...

18:54.322 --> 18:55.767
For Emma?

18:57.303 --> 18:58.554
I taught him that.

18:59.687 --> 19:01.099
Raised him right.

19:02.471 --> 19:04.157
Is there any money for that?

19:08.901 --> 19:11.013
So, aunt Betty, what do you say?

19:11.479 --> 19:14.371
Start over? Accept us as we are?

19:19.405 --> 19:20.618
God no!

19:20.619 --> 19:23.419
You people are a pack of animals.

19:26.508 --> 19:28.133
<i>So what do you think?</i>

19:28.134 --> 19:30.654
- Everyone live up to your expectations?
- Pretty much.

19:30.655 --> 19:32.458
And now I totally get why
you're a little gun-shy

19:32.459 --> 19:33.897
about the whole wedding thing.

19:34.392 --> 19:36.735
Okay, folks, let's do this.

19:36.736 --> 19:39.566
So I'd like to call on
Emma's two amazing godfathers.

19:39.567 --> 19:40.882
- Ready to go, dude.
- We're on it.

19:40.883 --> 19:42.982
- Her one incredible godmother.
- That's me.

19:43.675 --> 19:45.993
Her two one-of-a-kind
grandparents.

19:45.994 --> 19:48.098
- Aww, we love you.
- Aww, yes, we do.

19:48.099 --> 19:49.728
We love you.

19:49.729 --> 19:52.720
And hopefully a new step-granddad?

19:52.721 --> 19:54.252
Hey, baby girl.

19:54.859 --> 19:57.205
So we're gathered here to make a promise

19:57.536 --> 19:59.325
that we will always watch over her

19:59.326 --> 20:01.254
and make sure that she's always loved

20:01.255 --> 20:02.754
and happy and protected.

20:03.214 --> 20:05.115
And that she knows that she's
never alone in this world.

20:06.466 --> 20:08.180
We may be loud and crazy

20:08.181 --> 20:11.294
and anything but a typical,
normal American family,

20:11.295 --> 20:13.423
but we'll always be there for you.

20:15.129 --> 20:16.146
Danny.

20:16.658 --> 20:18.435
Okay, here we go.

20:18.436 --> 20:19.599
Here we go.

20:23.700 --> 20:25.392
- Oh.
- Oh.

20:25.393 --> 20:26.443
Emma.

20:26.444 --> 20:27.442
And just remember

20:27.443 --> 20:29.117
whenever you need a moral
or spiritual guide...

20:29.432 --> 20:30.443
You just come to me.

20:30.784 --> 20:32.157
- No, she would come to me.
- What?

20:34.236 --> 20:36.560
We're the only solid relationship here.

20:36.963 --> 20:38.811
Oh, we love you, Emma.

20:45.334 --> 20:47.032
Good news, guys.

20:47.033 --> 20:48.608
Our mailbox is, once again,

20:48.609 --> 20:50.777
stuffed with envelopes full of cash.

20:50.778 --> 20:52.622
But this time they're all for Ben.

20:53.072 --> 20:54.298
Yay rent.

20:54.749 --> 20:56.075
Mom?

20:56.076 --> 20:57.647
What did you do now?

20:57.648 --> 21:00.427
Well, that christening
announcement thing went so well.

21:00.428 --> 21:02.204
I thought I'd give it another go.

21:02.205 --> 21:04.555
Thank you, but I think Emma's had enough.

21:04.556 --> 21:06.866
Oh no no. Not Emma. You.

21:07.507 --> 21:12.438
Congratulations,
Ben, you're having a Bar Mitzvah!

